497
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:02,920
No. There's just this one, and a folk bar upstairs.
不，隻有一個，樓上有一個民間酒吧

498
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:06,560
And a trattoria with divine mezzes. That's where we're going.
還有一家擁有神韻的小餐館，就是我們要去的地方

499
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,840
I live here, of course. But that's it.
我就住在這裏，但僅此而已

500
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:11,160
Doesn't it get loud at night?
晚上不吵嗎？

501
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:15,040
It used to.
以前很吵

502
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:19,560
They used to play the drums at the folk bar. Made quite a ruckus.
他們以前在民謠酒吧打鼓

503
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:22,840
So I went and had a word with them.
所以我去和他們溝通了一下

504
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,680
We came to terms. They're much quieter now.
我們達成了協議  他們現在安靜得多

505
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:28,280
You get used to it after a while. They all close after 2 AM.
一段時間後你就習慣了，它們都在淩晨2點後關閉

506
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,600
Only ones left are me and the kids.
隻有我和孩子們

507
00:38:30,680 --> 00:38:32,640
There's no one else in the building.
冇有別人住在這裏了

508
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:36,360
Truly wonderful. Must be so much fun. So full of life.
真的太棒了，生活如此充實一定很有趣

509
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:38,080
Agah...
阿加

510
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:40,050
How about we go in there for a start?
我們過去吧，怎麼樣？

511
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:42,560
The music's so loud. We won't even hear each other.
音樂省廳很大，我都聽不到你說話

512
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:44,600
They're playing rock 'n roll!
他們在玩搖滾！

513
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:48,800
It's been such a long time since I've had some beer in Beyo?lu.
我已經很久冇在貝尤魯喝啤酒了

514
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:50,680
Let's start there. We can go upstairs later.
讓我們從那裏開始  等下再上樓

515
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:51,960
Sure. Alright. After you.
當然可以，你先清

516
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:03,920
They've found whose the DNA from the cat costume belongs to.
他們匹配到了貓服裝的DNA來源

517
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,760
- Is the SWAT team on the way? - Yes.
-特警隊出發了嗎？-是

518
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:08,840
To you.
敬你

519
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:11,120
- To you. - To you.
-敬你  -敬你

520
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,160
Life's a beautiful thing, isn't it?
生活真美好，不是嗎？

521
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:19,640
It is.
是的

522
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,360
- We're almost there. - Tell them to hold until we're there.
-我們快到了  -告訴他們在我們到之前不要行動

523
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:37,840
Tell the SWAT team not to go in until we're on the scene.
告訴特警隊在我們到現場前不要行動

524
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:41,960
I have a question.
我有個問題

525
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:46,480
How did you come up with the idea to write a book named "Life is Traffic"?
你是怎麼想到寫一本名為《生活就是交通》的書的？

526
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:49,920
- How do you think? - I wouldn't know.
-你怎麼看？  -我不知道

527
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,560
I was in a traffic accident.
我經曆過一次交通事故

528
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:55,320
I lost my husband in that accident.
我在那次事故中失去了丈夫

529
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:58,920
I was in the hospital for 11 months.
我在醫院待了11個月

530
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:02,360
The doctors told me I'd never walk again.
醫生告訴我，我也許不能再走路了

531
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:05,600
But I met you while doing the tango.
但是我在跳探戈時遇見了你

532
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:07,320
Indeed...
確實

533
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:16,760
Everything fell into place after that accident.
事故發生後，一切都井然有序

534
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:19,560
I realized how simple life is.
我意識到生活多麼簡單

535
00:40:19,640 --> 00:40:21,840
As simple as a traffic accident.
像交通事故一樣簡單

536
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:24,400
As simple as traffic.
像交通一樣簡單

537
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,800
I love the image of...
我喜歡……

538
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,560
The image of road signs.
道路標誌的圖像

539
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:34,400
"Stay out." "No u-turns." Stuff like that.
“呆在外麵”  “不要掉頭”這樣的東西

540
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:37,680
We carry those road signs around with us.
我們隨身攜帶這些路標

541
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:42,760
Stop. Go. You can park here. You can't park here.
停車  開車  你可以在這裏停車  你不能在這裏停車

542
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:49,520
The rules for traffic, Agah, turn out to be the rules for life.
交通規則變成了生活規則   阿加

543
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:07,760
Open up! Police!
開門！警察！

544
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:09,760
How did the accident happen?
那場意外是怎麼發生的？

545
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:16,120
- My husband broke a rule. - Which one?
-我丈夫違反了交通規則  -什麼規則？

546
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:23,960
Fuck!
他媽的！

547
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,600
Sefa, it's me, Firuz!
塞法，是我，菲魯茲！

548
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:36,240
Tell the team to pull back. I'm opening the door.
告訴特警隊後退  我來開門

549
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,400
Firuz...
菲魯茲

550
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,320
If you want to commit suicide together,
如果你想和某人一起自殺

551
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:49,360
the first rule is you should ask the other person
第一條規則是你應該先問對方

552
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,800
whether they want to die, as well.
他們是否也想死

553
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,440
Firuz, are you alright?
菲魯茲，你還好嗎？

554
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:16,920
Did he do it on purpose?
他是故意這樣做的嗎？

555
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:20,760
The worst part is, I knew what he was when I got married to him.
最糟糕的是，我嫁給他時就知道他是什麼人

556
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:23,920
I thought I could heal him. But...
我以為可以治愈他

557
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:28,240
- Whom can you truly heal, right? - Right...
-但又有誰能真正治愈別人呢？  -是的

558
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,280
Firuz...
菲魯茲

559
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,440
Sefa...
塞法

560
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:42,400
I have a gun pointed at me. Tell the team to pull back.
有槍指著我  讓特警隊後退

561
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:44,200
Alright.
好的

562
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,800
Lower your weapons. Lower your weapons.
放下武器  放下武器

563
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:55,000
- What does he want? - I don't know. I'm about to find out.
-兇手想要什麼？-我不知道  我正在問

564
00:42:55,600 --> 00:42:57,360
I'm closing then door now. Alright?
我要關門了  好嗎？

565
00:42:58,120 --> 00:42:59,320
Hold on, Sefa!
等等  塞法！

566
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:10,640
Pull back. Pull back.
後退  後退

567
00:43:11,560 --> 00:43:12,560
Back!
往後退！

568
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:18,000
But I have no doubt 
但我確信

569
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,720
that people have been healed after reading your book.
讀完你的書後人們就已經康複了

570
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:22,920
Perhaps...
也許

571
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:26,680
But I didn't write the book for them.
但是我冇有為別人寫這本書

572
00:43:26,760 --> 00:43:30,000
I wrote the book to heal myself.
我寫這本書是為了治愈自己

573
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:34,920
If they want to heal themselves, they need to write books of their own.
如果他們想自愈，就需要自己寫書

574
00:43:51,240 --> 00:43:54,760
Speak! Where the fuck did you hide the money? Speak!
說話！你他媽的把錢藏在哪裏？

575
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:57,760
Speak or you get one in the head! Speak!
說話還是吃槍子！快說！

576
00:44:01,240 --> 00:44:03,240
Did you write any other books?
你還寫其他書嗎？

577
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,520
No...
冇有

578
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,960
I'm still in the investigation part.
我還在構思

579
00:44:09,840 --> 00:44:13,480
- What is it about? - Agah Beyo?lu.
-關於什麼的？-阿加·貝尤魯

580
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:17,240
What do you mean? Why?
什麼意思？為什麼？

581
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:20,640
Because something tells me...
因為直覺告訴我……

582
00:44:21,280 --> 00:44:23,520
That nothing is as it seems.
冇有什麼是錶裏如一的

583
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:57,880
Yes, chief. Alright.
是的，長官

584
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:01,680
Alright, chief. We're waiting outside.
好的長官  我們在外麵等

585
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:03,520
Alright, chief. Of course.
好的長官  當然

586
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:15,680
It's Firuz! Don't shoot, I'm coming out!
我是菲魯茲！別開槍，我要出來！

587
00:45:31,440 --> 00:45:34,800
Excuse me. There was a small problem.
不好意思  我遇到一點小麻煩

588
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,000
I had two bullets jammed in my gun.
我的槍裏有兩發子彈

589
00:45:40,520 --> 00:45:43,200
- Lower your fucking weapons. - I'm glad.
-放下你的武器  -很高興你冇事

590
00:45:44,720 --> 00:45:47,720
I heard you on the radio and came straight over. He fell on me.
我在無線電裏聽到消息直接就過來，但被他擒住了

591
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:52,200
But I have bad news. He isn't the guy you're looking for.
但是我有個壞消息  他不是你要找的人

592
00:45:52,280 --> 00:45:53,160
What do you mean?
什麼意思？

593
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:54,480
He was a hired gun.
他是受雇的槍手

594
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:59,320
He knew there was a serial killer running around in a cat costume.
他知道有一個連環殺手穿著貓服裝到處殺人

595
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:01,480
He decided to become a cat and catch himself a mouse.
因此他決定成為一隻貓，捉住自己的老鼠

596
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:03,920
- I'm leaving, then. - Where to?
-我要走了-要去哪裏？

597
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,560
- I'll tell you afterwards. - Alright.
-我待會告訴你-好吧

598
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:13,720
- You scared us. - Why would you be scared?
-你嚇到我們了  -怎麼會嚇到你？

599
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,160
The devil looks after his own.
魔鬼會照顧自己

600
00:46:39,640 --> 00:46:41,640
I'm here to see Dr. Nedim Do?ru.
我來找內迪姆·多姆醫生

601
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:43,520
Do you have an appointment?
你有預約嗎？

602
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:49,440
A moment please.
請稍等

603
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:54,480
So he hung himself. I knew that's how it would end.
我知道他是上吊自殺的

604
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,920
- Where have you been? - Excuse me?
-你幹嘛去了？  -什麼？

605
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:00,920
I've been waiting for you for ten years.
我等你十年了

606
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,520
What do you mean?
什麼意思？

607
00:47:02,600 --> 00:47:07,200
I've been waiting for a cop to come asking about Ufuk Terazi.
我一直在等警察來詢問我關於烏福克·泰拉齊的事情

608
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:08,760
Then...
那麼……

609
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:10,840
Why didn't you go to the police?
你怎麼不去報警

610
00:47:11,520 --> 00:47:14,920
You wouldn't be asking me that if you knew how this report was made.
如果你知道這份報告是怎麼寫出來的，你就不會問我這個問題了

611
00:47:16,760 --> 00:47:20,320
I had just been assigned to Kambura. To the state hospital there.
我那時剛被分配到坎佈拉的國立醫院

612
00:47:21,240 --> 00:47:23,600
Something horrible had happened. It was before my time.
在我去之前發生了一件可怕的事

613
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:26,640
A fire. A house had burned down.
發生了一起火災，一棟房子被燒毀了

614
00:47:27,280 --> 00:47:28,960
The family inside had perished.
房子裏麵的人都死了

615
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:33,680
They brought Ufuk to me. His father did.
他父親把烏福克帶到我這裏

616
00:47:35,160 --> 00:47:37,040
Ufuk didn't want to talk at first.
烏福克一開始不想說話

617
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:42,800
But when he realized I wasn't a Kamburan, he opened up.
但是當他知道我不是坎佈蘭人時，他開了口

618
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,720
He told the same story over and over again.
他一遍又一遍地講同一個故事

619
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:49,720
I burned the house down, he said. I didn't believe him at first.
他說：是我把房子燒了  我一開始不相信他

620
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:55,280
I thought the trauma had altered his perception of reality.
我以為創傷改變了他對現實的看法

621
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:59,320
But how detailed it all was told me he wasn't hallucinating.
但是他說的那些細節告訴我他並冇有出現幻覺

622
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:03,240
He wasn't lying, either. So I called the police.
他也冇說謊  所以我找來了警察

623
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:06,440
I told them what happened, just as I'm telling you now.
我告訴他們發生了什麼事，就像我現在告訴你的那樣

624
00:48:06,520 --> 00:48:07,960
I told them Ufuk confessed.
我告訴他們烏福克認罪了

625
00:48:08,520 --> 00:48:12,000
One day, when I was on night shift, a man came to see me.
有一天，當我夜班時，一個男人來找我

626
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:14,520
I remember every word he said to me.
我記得他對我說的每句話

627
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:16,160
"You will forget all about this."
“你會忘記這一切”

628
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:18,480
"Or you disappear," he said.
“或者你從人間消失，”他說

629
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:23,520
"What do you mean, disappear?" I asked.
我問“你是什麼意思，消失？”

630
00:48:24,400 --> 00:48:27,800
"You'll disappear the same way people all around this country do."
“你將以這個國家的人們消失的方式消失”

631
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:31,920
I got what he meant then.
那時候我明白了他的意思

632
00:48:33,280 --> 00:48:34,880
He told me I was to write a report.
他要我寫一份報告

633
00:48:35,960 --> 00:48:37,200
So I did.
所以我就照做了

634
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:40,880
Who was he?
他是誰？

635
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:42,840
I don't know.
我不知道

636
00:48:43,400 --> 00:48:45,480
You never asked who he was? What he did?
你從來冇有問過他是誰，他是做什麼的？

637
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:50,840
Look, Nevra. I'll explain it to you this way...
內芙拉  我這樣跟你說吧……

638
00:48:51,640 --> 00:48:54,240
Conmen prey on hope.
騙子以希望為食

639
00:48:55,920 --> 00:48:57,760
A conman comes to you:
騙子來找你說：

640
00:48:57,840 --> 00:49:01,000
"Give me a dollar and I'll give you ten back."
“給我一塊錢，我會給你十塊錢”

641
00:49:01,720 --> 00:49:06,760
And if you're greedy by nature, you get hopeful and give him the dollar.
如果你天生貪婪，你就會滿懷希望給他錢

642
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:10,400
But the conmen of this country stopped selling hope.
但是這個國家的騙子們不再販售希望

643
00:49:11,880 --> 00:49:13,040
There's an easier way.
有一個更簡單的方法

644
00:49:15,080 --> 00:49:17,760
People are so afraid of you...
如果人們很怕你……

645
00:49:18,320 --> 00:49:21,880
Tell someone you're a cop on the phone, and they'll give you every dime.
在電話上告訴某人你是警察，他們會把所有錢都給你

646
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:29,520
If the conmen of a country con you through not hope but fear,
如果一個國家的騙子不是通過希望而是通過恐懼來欺騙你

647
00:49:30,320 --> 00:49:35,400
you never ask them who they are or what they do for a living.
你永遠不會問他們他們是誰，或者問他們以什麼為生

648
00:49:42,440 --> 00:49:43,440
Then...
那麼……

649
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:47,280
Could you identify him if you saw him?
如果看到他，你能認出他嗎？

650
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:50,280
Actually...
其實

651
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:51,920
I was really scared that night.
那天晚上我真的很害怕

652
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:55,200
I couldn't even look him in the eye.
我甚至不敢看他的眼睛

653
00:49:56,040 --> 00:49:58,680
But you can never tell.
但你永遠不知道

654
00:49:58,760 --> 00:50:02,120
You can never tell what someone might suddenly remember.
你永遠不知道別人會突然想起什麼

655
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:05,160
- Not even I can. - Give me a second.
-我也不能  -稍等一下

656
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:24,520
- I don't have to be afraid anymore? - You don't.
-我不必再害怕了？  -不用

657
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:04,920
- What did he do? - He was a judge.
-他做了什麼？-他生前是法官

658
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:07,040
Heavy penal court.
重刑法官

659
00:51:14,200 --> 00:51:15,680
After all these years...
這些年來

